on to the last thing, sort of the most recent thing

00:09:03.070 --> 00:09:04.000
that I've made.

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:06.610
And I've been working on a lot, um, is

00:09:06.610 --> 00:09:10.060
this app, uh, called Anasota, which is

00:09:10.060 --> 00:09:12.040
, uh, it started as a blue sky client, a

00:09:12.090 --> 00:09:13.940
very unique blue sky client.

00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:16.280
I call it a, a new, more peaceful, uh

00:09:16.280 --> 00:09:20.650
, social interface that helps you be offline more and online better

00:09:20.700 --> 00:09:20.990
.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:23.290
And, uh, Anasota was really asking the questions

00:09:23.660 --> 00:09:27.000
of what social media might could look like if I tried,

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:29.510
like, rethinking things from the ground up from a more

00:09:29.510 --> 00:09:30.990
, like, artsy, creative perspective.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.420
Um, and it, it all started, uh, literally

00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:37.440
, I guess I had this idea, I guess a little

00:09:37.700 --> 00:09:39.000
over a year ago.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.170
I posted this on blue sky, I said, we need

00:09:41.170 --> 00:09:44.060
an extremely weird and avant-garde blue sky client,

00:09:44.070 --> 00:09:45.990
and I think I'm gonna have to build it myself.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.180
Uh, so when I started working on it, I started

00:09:48.180 --> 00:09:51.060
brainstorming ideas and wondering what, what could I, what

00:09:51.760 --> 00:09:53.000
direction could I take this in?

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.000
And, and what should I call it?

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:54.990
And all these different things.

