And I started looking to other areas of my life for inspiration

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:00.770
, and, uh, one of those areas was, uh

00:10:00.800 --> 00:10:03.770
, my more recent interest in going mothing and, uh

00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:04.950
, learning about moths.

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:07.830
Uh, so, so during the warmer months, I've

00:10:08.010 --> 00:10:11.990
started going out into my yard and other places and taking lights

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:15.240
and cameras with me and creating these light traps that moss will

00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:16.000
be attracted to at night.

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:18.630
Um, it usually ranges from, like, starting at,

00:10:18.690 --> 00:10:19.650
like, 10 p.

00:10:19.650 --> 00:10:20.000
m.

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:21.170
and going into, like, 3 a.

00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:21.440
m.

00:10:21.440 --> 00:10:22.000
at night.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:23.700
Um, but I'll, yeah, set up my cameras

00:10:23.850 --> 00:10:26.160
and all that kind of stuff and document them and just learn

00:10:26.230 --> 00:10:27.000
about moss.

00:10:27.000 --> 00:10:28.960
And, uh, yeah, now I've, I've

00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:31.780
, I've seen so many different types of moths just

00:10:31.850 --> 00:10:33.000
in my backyard.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:35.570
It's really incredible to see the range and diversity of what

00:10:35.570 --> 00:10:37.000
you can see in your backyard.

00:10:37.000 --> 00:10:40.580
Um, so from there, I started thinking, what,

00:10:40.580 --> 00:10:43.000
uh, what could I name my app?

00:10:43.000 --> 00:10:46.000
And I really started honing in on moths.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:47.990
And this is the Anasota moth.

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:50.710
This is an oakworm moth by its more common name

00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:51.000
.

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:54.000
And this, this particular photo is a photo I took.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:55.520
This is a moth that showed up on my front door

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:55.990
one day.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:58.270
I woke up, I went outside, and this was on

00:10:58.340 --> 00:10:59.000
my door.

00:10:59.010 --> 00:11:00.000
I'd never seen one before.

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:02.280
It has these two little white dots, and it's very

00:11:02.390 --> 00:11:03.000
orange.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:05.000
It's very cute and fuzzy.

00:11:05.000 --> 00:11:06.000
I just fell in love with it.

00:11:06.010 --> 00:11:07.000
It's probably my favorite moth now.

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:08.000
And so I was like, that's it.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:08.990
That's what I'm gonna call the app.

00:11:09.000 --> 00:11:13.000
Um, and so I started really going deep into moths

00:11:13.000 --> 00:11:15.990
and learning all about them and all these different things.

